                            Hunger Free and Zero Food Waste.In addition to its important economic and societal impact,
                            food waste places undue pressure on finite natural resources and the environment. The
                            economic costs of this food wastage are substantial and amount to about $1 trillion each
                            year. Food that is harvested but ultimately lost or wasted consumes about one-quarter of all
                            water used by agriculture each year and requires a cropland area the size of China.
                        </p>
                        <p>Also,
                            Food waste generates about 8% of global greenhouse gas emissions annually and it is the
